{{menutrail|Main menu|Options menu|Display options}}
[[File:DynamicLightOptions.png|thumb|The display options menu in [[KDiZD]].]]
The '''dynamic lights options''' menu allows to modify the settings governing [[:Category:Dynamic_light|dynamic lights]]. Its [[MENUDEF]] name is {{c|GLLightOptions}}, a holdover from when dynamic lights were exclusive to the OpenGL renderer.

*'''{{LE|Dynamic Lights enabled}}''' (Yes/No)
:{{c|{{CVAR|R|gl_lights}}}}
:Enables or disables the entire dynamic light subsystem.
*'''{{LE|Enable light definitions}}''' (Yes/No)
:{{c|{{CVAR|R|gl_attachedlights}}}}
:Enables or disables light binding through [[GLDEFS]]. This setting is without effect at the moment.
*'''{{LE|Clip lights}}''' (Yes/No)
:{{c|{{CVAR|R|gl_lights_checkside}}}}
:If enabled, this option prevents dynamic lights from showing through planes. However, walls still have no effects.
*'''{{LE|Lights affect sprites}}''' (Yes/No)
:{{c|{{CVAR|R|gl_light_sprites}}}}
:If enabled, this option lets [[sprite]]s be affected by dynamic lights.
*'''{{LE|Lights affect particles}}''' (Yes/No)
:{{c|{{CVAR|R|gl_light_particles}}}}
:If enabled, this option lets [[particles]] be affected by dynamic lights.
*'''{{LE|Force additive lighting}}''' (Yes/No)
:{{c|{{CVAR|R|gl_lights_additive}}}}
:If enabled, all dynamic lights are additive. This improves performances, but degrades image quality.
*'''{{LE|Light intensity}}''' (0&mdash;1.0 by 0.1 increments)
:{{c|{{CVAR|R|gl_lights_intensity}}}}
:Selects how strong dynamic lights shine. This scales the lights' own intensity property.
*'''{{LE|Light size}}''' (0&mdash;2.0 by 0.1 increments)
:{{c|{{CVAR|R|gl_lights_size}}}}
:Selects how wide dynamic lights spread. This is also affected by the intensity.
*'''{{LE|Use shaders for lights}}''' (Yes/No)
:{{c|{{CVAR|R|gl_dynlight_shader}}}}
:If enabled, pixel shaders are used to render dynamic lights.

